The paper deals with analyzing spatial data and providing means for exploratory analysis, which falls under the scope of databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The approach involves capturing implicit feedback through mouse moves and explicit interaction with data points, which can be seen as a form of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the efficiency and effectiveness of the approach through realistic examples, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social computing (cs.SI).
